article.headline: High Point 92, NC Asheville 73
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Zione White scored 20 points to lead five players -- three of them off the bench -- in double-digit scoring and lift High Point to a 92-73 win against North Carolina-Asheville on Wednesday. The Panthers (8-8, 3-0 South Conference) got double-doubles from Danny Gathings (14 points, 10 rebounds) and from Patrick Hilliman, who posted 12 points and 10 rebounds off the bench. Mark Wilson added 15 points and Akeem Scott tallied 10 points. Bryan McCullough scored 18 points off the bench to lead the Bulldogs (3-11, 0-3). Steven Rush added 14 points off the bench. High Point converted 22 Bulldogs turnovers into 23 points and shot 46.9 percent for the night. Each team scored 45 points off the bench.
